rComments: I'm not sure where these rave reviews are coming from. I had Professor Pal for first-year constitutional law (small group). His assignments were incredibly onerous, unclear, and he refused to provide any guidance/clarification. The final exam was impossible to finish - classmates were crying afterwards. I would NOT recommend him.

Excellent professor. Engaging. Insightful. Smart. Talks about current issues when teaching constitutional law II. Tons of reading (the whole text book) but can survive off in-lecture material, summaries and participation. Long six-hour take-home exam which seemed fair. One of my best experiences at uOttawa: being taught by this young, engaging prof
His slides are long and incredibly detailed. He throws a lot of material at you but he presents it fairly clearly. He also provides usefully practice problems.
Amazing Prof! Very straight forward, gives practice questions and takes them up in class.
Great prof. Easy to understand. Generates critical thought in his students by asking the right questions. All around good guy.
Great prof. Very knowledgable and personable, always engaging. I will be taking more courses from him in the future!

Ottawa is lucky to have recently acquired Michael Pal. You will learn a lot as he uses an effective, student-centred pedagogy, is super smart, and is very well spoken. Most impressively, he is very modest, personable, and has a very kind, approachable demeanour. His disposition mixed with his talent and professionalism make him an ideal choice.
